quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  4,52,"Those are they whom God has cursed; he whom God has cursed, thou wilt not find for him any helper"
  4,53,"Or have they a share in the Kingdom? If that is so, they do not give the people a single date-spot"
  4,54,"Or are they jealous of the people for the bounty that God has given them? Yet We gave the people of Abraham the Book and the Wisdom, and We gave them a mighty kingdom"
  4,55,"And some of them there are that believe, and some of them that bar from it; Gehenna suffices for a Blaze"
  4,56,"Surely those who disbelieve in Our signs -- We shall certainly roast them at a Fire; as often as their skins are wholly burned, We shall give them in exchange other skins, that they may taste the chastisement. Surely God is All-mighty, All-wise"
  4,57,"And those that believe, and do deeds of righteousness, them We shall admit to gardens underneath which rivers flow, therein dwelling forever and ever; therein for them shall be spouses purified, and We shall admit them to a shelter of plenteous shade"
  4,58,"God commands you to deliver trusts back to their owners; and when you judge between the people, that you judge with justice. Good is the admonition God gives you; God is All-hearing, All-seeing"
  4,59,"O believers, obey God, and obey the Messenger and those in authority among you. If you should quarrel on anything, refer it to God and the Messenger, if you believe in God and the Last Day; that is better, and fairer in the issue"